# SecondBrain Cloud — agent rules

READ `HANDOFF.md` (repo root) BEFORE doing anything. It is the single source of truth
for this project and overrides your defaults when they conflict.

Non-negotiables (full detail in HANDOFF.md):
- 🎨 GLASS THEME is MANDATORY on every `/app/*` page — `.sb-dashboard` wrapper +
  `dash-panel dash-grain dash-interactive` panels + `--dash-*` tokens. Portalled
  overlays use ROOT tokens (`--bg-elev-3`, `--surface-2`, `--border-bright`,
  `--text-primary`, `--accent`, `--shadow-3`), always opaque. Reference:
  `src/components/dashboard/StatCard.tsx`.
- 🚫 NO DUMMY DATA — honest empty/zero states, real data only. Never fabricate
  numbers, curves, counts, or always-on indicators.
- This is Next.js 16 (breaking changes vs. your training) — check
  `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing Next-specific code.
- Run `npm run build` and `npx vitest run` before claiming done; add tests for new work.
- Never use "Hermes"/"gstack"/"GBrain" in user-facing copy (internal identifiers only).
- Git: feature branches + PRs, never commit secrets, always exclude
  `.vscode/settings.json`, stage specific files (never `git add .`).
